  <body>
    <segment id="1">
Snow on Christmas Eve
</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="22" relname="span">

The dream of many people of a white Christmas has partially come true this time in the Prignitz area.
</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="14" relname="evidence">  

Because on Christmas Eve, the landscape was covered in a blanket of snow.
</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="15" relname="concession">  

And even though most of it melted away again on the two public holidays,
</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="23" relname="span"> 

the children in particular were likely happy to have a proper festive celebration.
</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="27" relname="span">

By the way, for the second time in a row.
</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="26" relname="span">  

Because who doesn&apos;t remember the snowfall last year
</segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="25" relname="conjunction"> 

which reached the Prignitz in time for the festival
</segment>
    <segment id="17" parent="25" relname="conjunction"> 

and even created a winter landscape beyond the holidays?
</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="35" relname="span">  

So there can be no question that a white Christmas is a phenomenon of the past.
</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="34" relname="span">  

This year it reached far into the south.
</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="32" relname="span">  

Even in Mallorca there was snow for the holiday - 
</segment>
    <segment id="18" parent="7" relname="concession"> 

albeit only at 1000 meters altitude.
</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="33" relname="span">  

Elsewhere, the festival is always celebrated in scorching heat - 
</segment>
    <segment id="19" parent="8" relname="interpretation"> 

unimaginable for us.
</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="36" relname="joint">  

At least the people in those regions are spared the inclement weather on the streets.
</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="20" relname="condition">  

However, according to the police report,
</segment>
    <segment id="20" parent="29" relname="span"> 

the consequences in the Prignitz region were limited.
</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="30" relname="disjunction">  

Most people were probably prepared for the change in weather.
</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="28" relname="span">  

or simply stayed at home.
</segment>
    <segment id="21" parent="12" relname="evaluation-s"> 

as is appropriate for Christmas.
</segment>
